When expanded, the panel should also provide access to advanced simulation controls, scenario management, recording tools, camera controls, weather (future), and playback history.

The timeline itself should resemble a finely engraved surveying ruler, with elegant graduations, decorative tick marks, and brass instrument detailing instead of a conventional digital slider.

Buttons should feel like precision mechanical controls—engraved brass buttons with subtle depth, satisfying hover animations, and tactile pressed states.

Like every other panel, the Simulation Control Bar should feature original hand-illustrated borders and decorative framing that seamlessly integrate it into the Heritage Atlas design system
